  "prompt": "I had a bar code for Jio sim but now it's showing REDEEMED what should I do?",
  "response": "If your Jio SIM bar code is showing as **REDEEMED**, it means that the code has already been used to activate a SIM card. Here\u2019s what you can do:\n\n### 1. **Check if You Activated the SIM**\n   - If you recently activated a Jio SIM using that bar code, the status will show as \"Redeemed.\" In this case, there\u2019s nothing to worry about. Just wait for the SIM to activate and start using it.\n\n### 2. **If Someone Else Redeemed It**\n   - If you did not activate the SIM and suspect that someone else has used your bar code, contact **Jio Customer Care** immediately. You can reach them via:\n     - **Call**: Dial **198** or **1800 889 9999** (toll-free).\n     - **Jio Chat**: Use the **MyJio app** and access the chat support feature.\n     - **Email**: Send an email to `support@jio.com` or `customer.care@jio.com`.\n   - Provide them with your bar code details, and they will investigate the issue.\n\n### 3. **Request a New Bar Code**\n   - If the issue is unresolved and the bar code was misused, you can request a new one. Visit the nearest **Jio Store** or contact **Jio Customer Care** for assistance.\n\n### 4. **Verify the Bar Code Source**\n   - Ensure you obtained the bar code from an official Jio source (e.g., Jio website, MyJio app, or authorized retailer) to avoid fraud or misuse.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance! \ud83d\ude0a",
